## Name Collect — Explained

This is a **filter tag auto-builder** feature, specifically designed as a convenience for **Webflow** users (though it works anywhere with the right setup).

---

### The Problem It Solves

In a normal filter setup, you'd manually write something like:

```html
<div class="demo-card" data-filter-name="mammals aquatic">
```

But in **Webflow**, collection lists are generated dynamically — you can't easily write a combined string like `"mammals aquatic"` directly on the parent element, because each category comes from a separate collection item rendered individually.

---

### How `[data-filter-name-collect]` Works

Instead of setting `data-filter-name` manually on the parent card, you place `data-filter-name-collect` attributes on **child elements** (typically inside a Webflow Collection List). The script then:

1. Scans all children that have `data-filter-name-collect`
2. Collects each of their values as tokens
3. Deduplicates them (so `"mammals mammals aquatic"` becomes `"mammals aquatic"`)
4. Writes the final combined string back to the **parent's** `data-filter-name` attribute automatically

---

### Concrete Example

**Before (what's in the HTML):**
```html
<div class="demo-card" data-filter-name="">
  <!-- Webflow renders a Collection List of categories -->
  <div data-filter-name-collect="mammals"></div>
  <div data-filter-name-collect="aquatic"></div>
  <div data-filter-name-collect="mammals"></div>  <!-- duplicate! -->
</div>
```

**After the script runs:**
```html
<div class="demo-card" data-filter-name="mammals aquatic">
  ...
</div>
```

The duplicate `"mammals"` is ignored, and the parent now has a clean, space-separated filter string ready to be matched by the filter system.

---

### Why This Is Useful

In Webflow, a product or card might belong to **multiple categories** pulled from a multi-reference field. Each reference renders as its own Collection Item in a list. Without this feature, you'd have no clean way to consolidate those into a single `data-filter-name` value on the card. This feature bridges that gap automatically.